Ernest -<br>
We missed each other by a few months.  I joined in Dec. 1967, went to MCRD San Diego in Jan. 1968, ITR and Radio School at Camp Pendleton and then 'Nam (3rd Batt./1st Marines).  As Tom says, you could've found a ton of guys who would've been glad to change places.  In some ways, I'm glad I went, but, believe me, you didn't miss much by not going.  Give yourself a break, you did what you could and nobody could ask for more.
